products.name: Basics To Advanced In React
products.overview: Master React from scratch to deployment with hands-on projects, covering hooks, routing, context, and more.
products.long_description: This comprehensive course takes you from the very basics of React to advanced concepts like custom hooks, performance optimization, and state management with Context and Redux. You'll build real-world projects along the way and learn how to structure scalable React applications, deploy them, and follow best practices. Whether you're just starting or aiming to polish your React skills, this course has it all.

products.name: Start your career with Django
products.overview: Start your journey with Django and learn to build secure, dynamic web apps using Python.
products.long_description: This beginner-friendly course introduces you to the Django framework, one of the most powerful and popular Python web frameworks. You'll learn about models, views, templates, admin panels, and how to connect databases. By the end of the course, you'll have built several working web applications and gained a strong foundation to move into more complex Django projects.

products.name: The Future of Design Systems
products.overview: Explore the evolution of design systems and how they're shaping modern UI/UX across platforms.
products.long_description: This forward-thinking course examines the next generation of design systems in the era of automation, accessibility, and cross-platform design. You'll learn about scalable design tokens, integration with Figma and codebases, component libraries, and real-world strategies for maintaining consistency in large applications. Ideal for designers, developers, and product teams looking to modernize their UI workflows.

products.name: The Complete Guide to Backend Development
products.overview: Become a backend pro by mastering databases, APIs, authentication, and server-side programming.
products.long_description: This full-fledged backend development course covers everything from the ground up. You'll learn Node.js, Express, MongoDB, PostgreSQL, RESTful APIs, authentication systems, error handling, and scalable architecture design. You'll also explore advanced topics like security, deployment, and cloud integration. Whether you're building APIs or full-stack applications, this course gives you the complete backend developer toolkit.

products.name: Build a Blockchain from Scratch in Go
products.overview: Learn blockchain fundamentals by coding a working blockchain from the ground up in Golang.
products.long_description: Dive deep into blockchain technology by building your own blockchain system entirely from scratch using Go. This course guides you through core concepts like blocks, hashing, proof-of-work, transactions, consensus mechanisms, and peer-to-peer networking. It's perfect for developers curious about how Bitcoin or Ethereum works under the hood. Prior Go experience is helpful but not mandatory.

products.name: Frontend Fastlane Plan With Projects
products.overview: A fast-track roadmap to frontend development with real-world projects, tools, and best practices.
products.long_description: This intensive frontend bootcamp is designed to take you from zero to job-ready with a project-based approach. Learn HTML, CSS, JavaScript, React, and modern build tools like Vite and Webpack. You'll complete multiple real-world projects that simulate actual work environments and get exposure to responsive design, version control, and UI/UX best practices. Ideal for beginners aiming for a frontend developer role.

products.name: Master the Code Review
products.overview: Learn how to conduct and participate in effective code reviews to improve code quality and collaboration.
products.long_description: This course teaches you the art and science of code reviews — a critical skill for any professional developer. You'll learn best practices for reviewing code in different programming languages, how to give and receive constructive feedback, spotting security and performance issues, and how to improve team communication. Includes real-world code examples, review tools, and reviewer checklists.

products.name: JavaScript Basics To Advance
products.overview: Master JavaScript from the ground up with Shubham — from basics to advanced concepts with hands-on examples.
products.long_description: Join me on a complete journey through modern JavaScript, starting from the core fundamentals like variables, loops, and functions, and advancing to topics like closures, promises, async/await, ES6+, and DOM manipulation. The course includes dozens of hands-on examples, challenges, and mini-projects to ensure you truly grasp each concept. Suitable for beginners and intermediate developers aiming to deepen their JS knowledge.

products.name: Python Deep Dive With Projects
products.overview: Master Python with hands-on projects covering core concepts, advanced features, and real-world applications.
products.long_description: This comprehensive course takes you deep into Python programming, covering data types, control flow, functions, OOP, error handling, and modules. It also dives into advanced topics like decorators, generators, file handling, and working with APIs. Through practical projects such as web scrapers, data processors, and automation scripts, you'll gain the skills needed to write clean and powerful Python code for real-world use.

products.name: Mastering Software Technique
products.overview: Sharpen your software engineering skills by learning techniques that enhance productivity, code quality, and architecture.
products.long_description: This course is designed to elevate your engineering mindset with software techniques used by top developers. Learn principles like SOLID design, modularity, test-driven development (TDD), clean code, design patterns, and system scalability. Ideal for intermediate developers who want to transition from writing just code to building maintainable and efficient software solutions.

products.name: Web Development Foundation
products.overview: A beginner-friendly course to learn HTML, CSS, and JavaScript from scratch and build responsive websites.
products.long_description: Kickstart your web development journey with this foundational course covering HTML5, CSS3, and modern JavaScript. You'll learn how the web works, create beautiful user interfaces, and bring interactivity to your sites. This course also includes responsive design, layout systems like Flexbox and Grid, and beginner projects like a portfolio and landing page. Perfect for absolute beginners.

products.name: Mastering Git and GitHub - A Practical Guide
products.overview: Learn Git and GitHub from the ground up through practical use cases and workflows used in real development teams.
products.long_description: Version control is a must-have skill for every developer. In this course, you'll learn how to use Git for local tracking, branching, and merging. You'll also explore GitHub for remote collaboration, pull requests, issue tracking, and contributing to open source. Includes hands-on scenarios and visual explanations of what’s happening behind the scenes. Ideal for beginners to intermediate developers.

products.name: Everything About React v16
products.overview: A complete guide to React v16 covering all major concepts including Hooks, state, props, and component lifecycle.
products.long_description: This course gives you a solid understanding of React v16, the popular frontend library from Meta. You'll learn about components, JSX, props, state management, hooks (like useState, useEffect), and the component lifecycle. It also includes routing with React Router, form handling, and simple API integration. Ideal for developers who want to build modern web apps using React 16.

products.name: Diving Deep With Python 2.7
products.overview: Explore the legacy of Python 2.7 and its features with hands-on coding exercises and comparisons to Python 3.
products.long_description: Though officially retired, Python 2.7 is still used in some legacy systems. This course provides a deep dive into Python 2 syntax, features, and libraries. You'll explore string formatting, exception handling, file I/O, and differences from Python 3. Useful for developers working with older codebases or maintaining existing systems. Includes practical scripts and backward compatibility tips.

products.name: Kickstart Your UI Design Career
products.overview: Learn the fundamentals of UI design and start building beautiful, user-friendly interfaces from day one.
products.long_description: This beginner-level course is your gateway into the world of UI design. You'll learn about visual hierarchy, typography, color theory, layout principles, and how to use popular tools like Figma or Adobe XD. Includes step-by-step UI redesign projects and portfolio creation guidance. Ideal for aspiring designers who want to build a career in digital product design.

cartList.name: Frontend Fastlane Plan With Projects
cartList.overview: A fast-track roadmap to frontend development with real-world projects, tools, and best practices.
cartList.long_description: This intensive frontend bootcamp is designed to take you from zero to job-ready with a project-based approach. Learn HTML, CSS, JavaScript, React, and modern build tools like Vite and Webpack. You'll complete multiple real-world projects that simulate actual work environments and get exposure to responsive design, version control, and UI/UX best practices. Ideal for beginners aiming for a frontend developer role.

cartList.name: The Complete Guide to Backend Development
cartList.overview: Become a backend pro by mastering databases, APIs, authentication, and server-side programming.
cartList.long_description: This full-fledged backend development course covers everything from the ground up. You'll learn Node.js, Express, MongoDB, PostgreSQL, RESTful APIs, authentication systems, error handling, and scalable architecture design. You'll also explore advanced topics like security, deployment, and cloud integration. Whether you're building APIs or full-stack applications, this course gives you the complete backend developer toolkit.

cartList.name: The Future of Design Systems
cartList.overview: Explore the evolution of design systems and how they're shaping modern UI/UX across platforms.
cartList.long_description: This forward-thinking course examines the next generation of design systems in the era of automation, accessibility, and cross-platform design. You'll learn about scalable design tokens, integration with Figma and codebases, component libraries, and real-world strategies for maintaining consistency in large applications. Ideal for designers, developers, and product teams looking to modernize their UI workflows.

cartList.name: Start your career with Django
cartList.overview: Start your journey with Django and learn to build secure, dynamic web apps using Python.
cartList.long_description: This beginner-friendly course introduces you to the Django framework, one of the most powerful and popular Python web frameworks. You'll learn about models, views, templates, admin panels, and how to connect databases. By the end of the course, you'll have built several working web applications and gained a strong foundation to move into more complex Django projects.
